## Database settings

Voxel requires **MySQL 8** or **MariaDB 10.3** or higher to run properly.

The database system is auto detected during installation.

However, if you decide to change the database system after installation, for example you switch from **MySQL** to **MariaDB** or vice versa, then you have to select the new version manually in **WP admin  Voxel  Settings  Database**.

Once you make the change, you have to recreate the Voxel index tables for your post types in **WP admin ** **Post types  Edit each post type  Filtering  Indexing status  Recreate table and index all posts**

In addition to changing database system, you can also control the number of post revisions that are stored in your site using **Max revision count (per post)** option.
